<p>Every organism responds to the world with an intricate cascade of biochemistry. There&rsquo;s a source of heat here, a faint scent of food there, or the crack of a twig as something moves nearby. Each stimulus can trigger the rise of one set of molecules in an animal&rsquo;s body and perhaps the fall of others. The effect ramifies, tripping feedback loops and flipping switches, until a bird leaps into the air...</p>
